{
  "doc_id": "17427",
  "text": "Murakawa and Takeuchi [CITATION_1] used DLC coating (Diamond-like carbon) on a ball that was slid against an aluminum sheet, and the COF was measured. Guillon et al. [CITATION_2] used other friction tests similar to that of Murakawa and Takeuchi; however, the slide tool had a cylindrical shape, and the authors performed surface topography analysis with different tool coatings.",
